          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the butter and dark brown sugar together until combined. Beat in the golden syrup and egg. Stir in the flour, spices, bicarbonate of soda, and salt until a firm dough forms. Divide into two discs, wrap, and refrigerate for 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cut and bake the panels",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Draw or print house templates on cardboard and cut out. Heat the oven to 170°C conventional (150°C fan). Roll the chilled dough to 4 to 5 mm thick on a lightly floured surface. Lay templates on the dough and cut around them with a sharp knife. Transfer to lined baking trays. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes per batch until even in colour and just firm; they harden further on cooling. Cool flat on a rack. Re-cut any panels that spread out of shape while still warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the icing and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the egg whites with the lemon juice until frothy. Add the icing sugar and beat until thick, smooth, and holds stiff peaks. Transfer to a piping bag. Pipe a thick line of icing along the joins and assemble the house in stages, holding or propping each section until it sets (10 to 15 minutes per join). Decorate the assembled house with remaining icing and sweets.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
